So what can this humble hypnotist do? Well, he is first asked to communicate with the cute little blonde munchkin herself. Seems the girl has become a slightly despondent mute since escaping the clutches of the kidnappers and no one has managed to break through to her. Dr. Strothers enters her mind and uncovers the disturbing vision of an old, shirtless man with a similar pentagram tatoo.<br>
<br>
The investigation proceeds while Dr.Strothers finds himself unable to sleep due to visions and overall paranoïa setting in. When it rains, it pours for our good Doctor as his pregnant wife gets more than a little suspicious about her husband's frequent late night trips and sudden insomnia. Add to this the murder of an informant/consultant along with the threats of his little girl being kidnapped and soon Dr.Strothers is on the edge of a nervous breakdown.<br>
<br>
The murders have something to do with black magic, but what exactly? Why is this blonde girl so important? And what's with the strange symbols she drew during one session? The answers will all be revealed in the end, as with every other police drama.<br>
<br>
Don't be fooled by the premise of black magic and hypnosis, this movie rarely dabbles in the surreal universe of a Lynch or even an Argento. Outside of a few CGI  dream sequences and the very visually appealing folding maze, the movie rarely makes any attempts at offering anything in the way of  a truly logic defying experience.<br>
<br>
One would hope then that the more &quot;realistic&quot; police drama portion make up for this. Unfortunately it doesn't quite manage to pull its own weight let alone cover for the other portion.<br>
<br>
A good police drama needs a few key elements in order to work, two of the most important ones being an interesting premise and a puzzling mystery filled with red herrings and false leads. Hypnotic delivers a somewhat cliché premise (even if it does so with a chilling opening scene) with its mysterious cult trying to kidnap an innocent victim/witness who won't/can't say a word about the criminals in question. It also loses point for a by the number approach to the story and an overall lack of red herrings or, for that matter, of actual clues. Hypnotic often relies on cheap parlour tricks revolving around Dr. Strothers' gift, alas, colourful and well shot CGI won't fool the critical eye for too long.<br>
<br>
Also, unlike some critics, I found the camera work to be banal at best. Most of the scenes were shot with a very standard approach. Unlike Argento's giallo movies with their experimental camera shots and odd angles, the director of Hypnotic seems content in keeping things simple to the point of being completely forgetable. I'll admit that the dream sequences were slick for the most part. They gave us hope that the director would spare us from the blandnes sof everything else in this movie.<br>
<br>
Speaking of bland, the actors were fairly tepid in their own rights. Most of them were more than capable in their roles, but lacked colour. Again, the characters seem almost typecasted and the family drama involving Dr.Strothers and his pregnant wife was sometimes laughable. For example, his discussion with the missus about sex and the lack thereof (an important issue for couples awaiting the birth of a child) didn't capture the interest of the audience at all. In fact, most of their heated arguments left me with the impression that I was watching a soap opera or, better yet, a typical Hollywood movie. In other words, no one seemed to care about their relationship despite the director's obvious desire to create a tense family drama.<br>
<br>
In the final analysis, Hypnotic isn't a bad police thriller, just a very bland one. Adding a slightly supernatural edge to it didn't help seeing as the audience left without even a single round of applause. I myself rose from my seat thinking that I had just watched a typical made for TV movie with slightly superior production value and acting. While Hypnotic won't put you to sleep, it won't help you stay awake either. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#330000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bescape96855.showUserPublicProfile?gid=asplagis>Asplagis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>vagabond</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font color=#ff6663>(8/11/03 11:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fescape96855frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fantasia 2003 - Reviews</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Rubber</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
